<subSubSection id="C30F0386B13FFF9AFF55FE1FFBE6FA8C" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13FFF9AFF55FE1FFB4FFC2C" blockId="10.[166,1225,506,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of face with facial carina; no ocellar setae; epistoma high, half as high as antennal groove; parafacial in profile 1.7 times as wide as flagellomere 1 (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFDDBFDDFFD15FDED" box="[597,659,570,597]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFD2CFDDFFD49FDEC" box="[674,719,570,596]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFD2CFDDFFD34FDEC" box="[674,690,570,596]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFD4FFDDFFD49FDEC" box="[705,719,570,596]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">7</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
), mesonotal scutum brownish yellow with extensive black lyrate pattern; anterior portions of anepisternum and anepimeron, as well as anteroventral part of katepisternum black (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFD1AFD9FFD6FFD2C" box="[660,745,634,661]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
fig. 5, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFD55FD9FFD6FFD2C" box="[731,745,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); scutellum with at least two pairs of long golden yellow setae (setae partly broken); wing 
<quantity id="4CEDFDE8B13FFF9AFD47FD7FFC9AFD0C" box="[713,796,666,692]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
long, grey, except yellow anterobasal margin and cell br, and large brown anteroapical spot; fore coxa unmodified; fore and mid trochanters without spinulose setulae; fore femur without long setae, except 2 subbasal ventral setae; setae in ventro-apical rows brown, spurious and moderately long (one-quarter to one-third as long as femur width); all femora mostly brown; tibia reddish or brownish yellow (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFF20FCDFFE81FCEC" box="[174,263,826,853]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
fig. 5, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFF77FCDFFE81FCEC" box="[249,263,826,852]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites brownish yellow, tergites 1–3 partly black (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFC79FCDFFBB5FCED" box="[1015,1075,826,853]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFBCFFCDFFBC9FCEC" box="[1089,1103,826,852]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">9</emphasis>
); sternites sparsely yellow setose; surstyli (exposed only in the 
<typeStatus id="54AEEEAFB13FFF9AFC8FFCBFFCE0FCCC" box="[769,870,858,884]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13FFF9AFC03FCBFFB8FFCCC" box="[909,1033,858,884]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brahma">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFC03FCBFFB8FFCCC" box="[909,1033,858,884]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">A. brahma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) long triangular (as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13FFF9AFF64FC9EFED2FC2C" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[234,340,890,916]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteola">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFF64FC9EFED2FC2C" box="[234,340,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">E. luteola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB13FFF9AFE06FC9FFDC7FC2C" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[392,577,890,916]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" pagination="219 - 233" refId="ref10531" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. A taxonomic revision of the genera Eupyrgota and Paradapsilia in Korea (Diptera: Pyrgotidae) // Korean Journal of Entomology. - 2000. - 30, N 4. - P. 219 - 233." type="book chapter" year="2000">Kim, Han, 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFDC7FC9FFD1EFC2D" box="[585,664,890,917]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">fig. 2G</figureCitation>
); most setae and setulae brown to reddish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13FFF9AFF55FC7FFD92FB0C" blockId="10.[166,1225,506,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
R e m a r k s. As the 
<typeStatus id="54AEEEAFB13FFF9AFE49FC7FFDBFFC0C" box="[455,569,922,948]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">holotypes</typeStatus>
of both nominal species are males (some sexually dimorphic characters remain unknown), the reason to place it in the nominative subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13FFF9AFF28FC3EFE9BFC4C" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[166,285,987,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFF28FC3EFE9BFC4C" box="[166,285,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.) is their large size and, in addition, spotted, as in many other Asian species of the nominative subgenus, wing pattern (rather than widely brown one, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13FFF9AFB3FFC1EFD82FB8C" authority="Aldrich" authorityName="Aldrich" authorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviseta" subGenus="Asipyrgota">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFB3FFC1EFB4FFBAC" box="[1201,1225,1019,1044]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">E.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFF3EFBFFFEABFB8C" box="[176,301,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Asipyrgota</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFEB1FBFFFE19FB8C" box="[319,415,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">flaviseta</emphasis>
Aldrich
</taxonomicName>
: see below). The specimens show no essential differences in size and body coloration; they share the dark pleural and wing patterns, brown coloration of the moderately thin femora, comparatively strong spurious setae of the apicoventral rows. I therefore consider both 
<typeStatus id="54AEEEAFB13FFF9AFD91FB9FFD17FB2C" box="[543,657,1146,1172]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">holotypes</typeStatus>
to be conspecific and synonymize two nominal species. No females are known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13FFF9AFF55FB5FFBE6FA8C" blockId="10.[166,1225,506,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
The paper by Hendel appeared in the beginning of 
<quantity id="4CEDFDE8B13FFF9AFCB9FB5FFC09FB6C" box="[823,911,1210,1236]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.86156" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" unit="in" value="1914.0">1914 in</quantity>
the volume of “Archiv für Naturgeschichte” for the year 1913, and Bezzi in his paper (published not earlier than in the August, 1914), referred to the species described by Hendel as to already published, with numbers of the pages. This undoubtedly shows the priority of the Hendel’s name.
</paragraph>
